### JITSymbol() {#a5e2004fd61cf36e9055255e0605ba2fd}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>llvm::JITSymbol::JITSymbol (<a href="#adcebe99ff32aee6ab6082e79b09ef503">GetAddressFtor</a> GetAddress, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/jitsymbolflags">JITSymbolFlags</a> Flags)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Create a symbol for a definition that doesn&#39;t have a known address yet.

<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="GetAddress">A functor to materialize a definition (fixing the address) on demand.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>
This constructor allows a JIT layer to provide a reference to a symbol definition without actually materializing the definition up front. The user can materialize the definition at any time by calling the getAddress method.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/jitsymbol-h/#l00296">296</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/jitsymbol-h">JITSymbol.h</a>.
